com.yahoo.bullet.record.avro

Class UntypedAvroBulletRecord

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.yahoo.bullet.record.BulletRecord<Serializable>
      • com.yahoo.bullet.record.UntypedBulletRecord
        • com.yahoo.bullet.record.avro.UntypedAvroBulletRecord
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Iterable<Map.Entry<String,Serializable>>

    public class UntypedAvroBulletRecord
extends UntypedBulletRecord
    An implementation of BulletRecord using Avro for serialization. It is an UntypedBulletRecord. By default, after serialization the record deserializes lazily. It will only deserialize when one of the get/set methods are called. This makes the object cheap to send through repeated read-write cycles without modifications. You can force a read by either calling a get/set method.
